1. Create a New Angular Project
If you haven't already, create a new Angular project by running:

ng new userManagementApp
cd userManagementApp


Install dependencies like Angular Forms for handling form data and Angular Router for navigation.

npm install @angular/forms @angular/router

2. Generate Components and Services
Generate the necessary components and a service:

ng generate component register

ng generate component login

ng generate component profile

ng generate service auth


3. Implement Routing

Update app-routing.module.ts to handle navigation between components



Add these routes to app.component.html to allow navigation


4. Build the Auth Service (auth.service.ts)
The AuthService will handle user data management (mocking a backend).


5. Build the Register Component (register.component.ts)
The Register Component allows new users to register.


6. Build the Login Component (login.component.ts)
The Login Component lets users log in.


Component Logic (login.component.ts):


7. Build the Profile Component (profile.component.ts)
The Profile Component displays the logged-in user's information.

Template (profile.component.html):

Component Logic (profile.component.ts):

8. Update app.module.ts
Ensure all the components and the FormsModule are declared in app.module.ts

9. Run the Application
Start your Angular application
